{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|2Ti|2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","chapter":2,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":1,"text":"You, therefore, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":2,"text":"What you have heard from me in the presence of many witnesses, commit to faithful men who will be able to teach others also.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":3,"text":"Share in suffering as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":4,"text":"No one serving as a soldier gets entangled in the concerns of civilian life; he seeks to please the commanding officer.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":5,"text":"Also, if anyone competes as an athlete, he is not crowned unless he competes according to the rules.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":6,"text":"The hardworking farmer ought to be the first to get a share of the crops.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":7,"text":"Consider what I say, for the Lord will give you understanding in everything.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":8,"text":"Remember Jesus Christ, risen from the dead and descended from David, according to my gospel,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":9,"text":"for which I suffer to the point of being bound like a criminal. But the word of God is not bound.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":10,"text":"This is why I endure all things for the elect: so that they also may obtain salvation, which is in Christ Jesus, with eternal glory.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":11,"text":"This saying is trustworthy:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":12,"text":"if we endure, we will also reign with him;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":13,"text":"if we are faithless, he remains faithful,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":14,"text":"Remind them of these things, and charge them before God not to fight about words. This is useless and leads to the ruin of those who listen.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":15,"text":"Be diligent to present yourself to God as one approved, a worker who doesn’t need to be ashamed, correctly teaching the word of truth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":16,"text":"Avoid irreverent and empty speech, since those who engage in it will produce even more godlessness,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":17,"text":"and their teaching will spread like gangrene. Hymenaeus and Philetus are among them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":18,"text":"They have departed from the truth, saying that the resurrection has already taken place, and are ruining the faith of some.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":19,"text":"Nevertheless, God’s solid foundation stands firm, bearing this inscription: The Lord knows those who are his, and let everyone who calls on the name of the Lord turn away from wickedness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":20,"text":"Now in a large house there are not only gold and silver vessels, but also those of wood and clay; some for honorable use and some for dishonorable.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":21,"text":"So if anyone purifies himself from anything dishonorable, he will be a special instrument, set apart, useful to the Master, prepared for every good work.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":22,"text":"Flee from youthful passions, and pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace, along with those who call on the Lord from a pure heart.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":23,"text":"But reject foolish and ignorant disputes, because you know that they breed quarrels.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":24,"text":"The Lord’s servant must not quarrel, but must be gentle to everyone, able to teach, and patient,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":25,"text":"instructing his opponents with gentleness. Perhaps God will grant them repentance leading them to the knowledge of the truth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","bookOrder":54,"chapter":2,"verse":26,"text":"Then they may come to their senses and escape the trap of the devil, who has taken them captive to do his will.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ti","chapter":2,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,8,12,13,14,20,22],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Be Strong in Grace"},{"beforeVerse":14,"text":"An Approved Worker"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ti:2:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You, therefore, my son, be strong in the grace "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 1:6","book":"Gal","chapter":1,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 3:18","book":"2Pe","chapter":3,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" that is in Christ Jesus. "}],"crossRefs